<div class="prog-page">
  <div style="margin-bottom:20px;"><h1 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:800;">Example: Informative Report ℹ️</h1>
  <p style="color:var(--prog-muted);font-size:13px;">Valid observation, but insufficient impact to qualify as a bug bounty finding.</p></div>
  <div class="prog-card">
    <div class="prog-card-header" style="background:#EBF8FF;">
      <div><h2 style="font-size:17px;font-weight:800;">Missing Content-Security-Policy and X-Frame-Options headers on all pages</h2>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-top:8px;"><span class="prog-badge prog-badge-gray">Low</span><span class="prog-badge prog-badge-blue">ℹ️ Informative</span></div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="prog-card-body">
      <div style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px;">The application does not set Content-Security-Policy or X-Frame-Options headers. These are security best practices but without a specific exploitable attack chain demonstrated, this is classified as informative.</div>
      <div style="background:#EBF8FF;border:1px solid #BEE3F8;border-radius:6px;padding:16px;">
        <div style="font-weight:700;color:#2A4365;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:6px;">Triage Response — Informative</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;color:#2C5282;">Thank you. Missing security headers are a valid observation but we require a demonstrated exploitable impact. If you can chain this with a concrete XSS or clickjacking attack with user impact, please resubmit. On its own, missing headers are informative only and do not qualify for a bounty. We have noted this for our security hardening backlog.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div style="margin-top:16px;display:flex;gap:10px;"><a href="/program/examples/not-applicable" class="prog-btn prog-btn-outline">Next: N/A →</a><a href="/program/submit" class="prog-btn prog-btn-green">Submit a Report →</a></div>
</div>
